<p>Sweet! Now go back to <code>/genus</code>.</p>
<h2 id="fetching-a-subset-of-genusscientist-results">Fetching a Subset of GenusScientist Results <a class="headerlink" href="easy-collection-filtering#fetching-a-subset-of-genusscientist-results" title="Permalink to this headline"><i class="fa fa-link" aria-hidden="true"></i></a></h2>
<p>We're already printing the number of scientists that each <code>Genus</code> has. <em>And</em>
thanks to a fancy query we made inside <code>GenusRepository</code>, that joins over and fetches
the related <code>User</code> data all at once... this entire page is built with one query:</p>
