<p>Try it now. Yes!</p>
<p>Click to check out the queries. It <em>still</em> makes a COUNT query for each row...
but wait: it <em>also</em> queries for <em>all</em> of the <code>genus_scientist</code> results for each
<code>genus</code>. That sucks! Even if a <code>Genus</code> only has two experts... we're fetching <em>all</em>
of the data for <em>all</em> of its genus scientists.</p>
<p>Why? Well, as soon as we loop over <code>genusScientists</code>:</p>
<p><div class="code-block-wrapper" data-code-block-guid="d0711565a7">
    <div class="meta">
        <div class="actions">
